TITLE: Implementing Client Connection Reducer in Rust
DESCRIPTION: Defines a reducer that handles client connections by creating or updating user records with online status. Uses ctx.db.user() methods to manage user data with appropriate error handling.
SOURCE: https://github.com/clockworklabs/spacetime-docs/blob/master/docs/modules/rust/quickstart.md#2025-04-18_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
#[reducer(client_connected)]
pub fn client_connected(ctx: &ReducerContext) {
    if let Some(user) = ctx.db.user().identity().find(ctx.sender) {
        ctx.db.user().identity().update(User { online: true, ..user });
    } else {
        ctx.db.user().insert(User {
            name: None,
            identity: ctx.sender,
            online: true,
        });
    }
}
```

