TITLE: Processing User Input in Rust for SpacetimeDB Chat Client
DESCRIPTION: This function reads user input from stdin, processes commands to set names or send messages, and invokes the appropriate reducers. It handles the main interaction loop for the chat client.
SOURCE: https://github.com/clockworklabs/spacetime-docs/blob/master/docs/sdks/rust/quickstart.md#2025-04-18_snippet_18

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
fn user_input_loop(ctx: &DbConnection) {
    for line in std::io::stdin().lines() {
        let Ok(line) = line else {
            panic!("Failed to read from stdin.");
        };
        if let Some(name) = line.strip_prefix("/name ") {
            ctx.reducers.set_name(name.to_string()).unwrap();
        } else {
            ctx.reducers.send_message(line).unwrap();
        }
    }
}
```

