TITLE: Generating Identity from OpenID Claims in Python
DESCRIPTION: Function that generates a SpacetimeDB identity by hashing OpenID Connect issuer and subject claims using BLAKE3. The function combines the hashed values with specific prefixes and checksums to create a 32-byte identity.
SOURCE: https://github.com/clockworklabs/spacetime-docs/blob/master/docs/index.md#2025-04-18_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
def identity_from_claims(issuer: str, subject: str) -> [u8; 32]:
   hash1: [u8; 32] = blake3_hash(issuer + "|" + subject)
   id_hash: [u8; 26] = hash1[:26]
   checksum_hash: [u8; 32] = blake3_hash([
      0xC2,
      0x00,
      *id_hash
   ])
   identity_big_endian_bytes: [u8; 32] = [
      0xC2, 
      0x00,
      *checksum_hash[:4],
      *id_hash
   ]
   return identity_big_endian_bytes
```

