TITLE: Implementing Process Thread for Database Updates in C#
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines a ProcessThread function that runs in a separate thread. It continuously processes database updates and user commands until signaled to exit, then closes the database connection.
SOURCE: https://github.com/clockworklabs/spacetime-docs/blob/master/docs/sdks/c-sharp/quickstart.md#2025-04-18_snippet_18

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
/// Our separate thread from main, where we can call process updates and process commands without blocking the main thread. 
void ProcessThread(DbConnection conn, CancellationToken ct)
{
    try
    {
        // loop until cancellation token
        while (!ct.IsCancellationRequested)
        {
            conn.FrameTick();

            ProcessCommands(conn.Reducers);

            Thread.Sleep(100);
        }
    }
    finally
    {
        conn.Disconnect();
    }
}
```

