TITLE: Implementing Client Connection Reducer
DESCRIPTION: Handles player connection logic by either moving a logged-out player to the active player table or creating a new player entry
SOURCE: https://github.com/clockworklabs/spacetime-docs/blob/master/docs/unity/part-3.md#2025-04-18_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
#[spacetimedb::reducer(client_connected)]
pub fn connect(ctx: &ReducerContext) -> Result<(), String> {
    if let Some(player) = ctx.db.logged_out_player().identity().find(&ctx.sender) {
        ctx.db.player().insert(player.clone());
        ctx.db
            .logged_out_player()
            .identity()
            .delete(&player.identity);
    } else {
        ctx.db.player().try_insert(Player {
            identity: ctx.sender,
            player_id: 0,
            name: String::new(),
        })?;
    }
    Ok(())
}
```

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
[Reducer(ReducerKind.ClientConnected)]
public static void Connect(ReducerContext ctx)
{
    var player = ctx.Db.logged_out_player.identity.Find(ctx.Sender);
    if (player != null)
    {
        ctx.Db.player.Insert(player.Value);
        ctx.Db.logged_out_player.identity.Delete(player.Value.identity);
    }
    else
    {
        ctx.Db.player.Insert(new Player
        {
            identity = ctx.Sender,
            name = "",
        });
    }
}
```

