TITLE: Implementing Client Disconnection Reducer
DESCRIPTION: Handles player disconnection by moving the active player to the logged out table
SOURCE: https://github.com/clockworklabs/spacetime-docs/blob/master/docs/unity/part-3.md#2025-04-18_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
#[spacetimedb::reducer(client_disconnected)]
pub fn disconnect(ctx: &ReducerContext) -> Result<(), String> {
    let player = ctx
        .db
        .player()
        .identity()
        .find(&ctx.sender)
        .ok_or("Player not found")?;
    let player_id = player.player_id;
    ctx.db.logged_out_player().insert(player);
    ctx.db.player().identity().delete(&ctx.sender);

    Ok(())
}
```

