TITLE: Logging in C# with SpacetimeDB
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use the Log class in SpacetimeDB for writing to a private debug log. It includes examples of different log levels and shows how to log information about users and their dog counts.
SOURCE: https://github.com/clockworklabs/spacetime-docs/blob/master/docs/modules/c-sharp/index.md#2025-04-18_snippet_29

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
using SpacetimeDB;

public static partial class Module {
    [Table(Name = "user")]
    public partial struct User {
        [PrimaryKey]
        uint Id;
        [Unique]
        string Username;
        ulong DogCount;
    }

    [Reducer]
    public static void LogDogs(ReducerContext ctx) {
        Log.Info("Examining users.");

        var totalDogCount = 0;

        foreach (var user in ctx.Db.user.Iter()) {
            Log.Info($"    User: Id = {user.Id}, Username = {user.Username}, DogCount = {user.DogCount}");

            totalDogCount += user.DogCount;
        }

        if (totalDogCount < 300) {
            Log.Warn("Insufficient dogs.");
        }

        if (totalDogCount < 100) {
            Log.Error("Dog population is critically low!");
        }
    }
}
```

